\f0\fs24 \cf0 # Miraculous AI\
\
Miraculous AI is a kid-friendly chat assistant inspired by the world of "Miraculous: Tales of Ladybug & Cat Noir." Designed for young users, it helps them learn how to interact with AI in a fun and educational way. The assistant provides responses to questions and engages kids with a playful and interactive experience.\
\
## Features\
- **Miraculous Theme:** Styled with references to Ladybug and Cat Noir, making it enjoyable for young fans.\
- **Typewriter-Style Responses:** Chat responses appear one letter at a time, creating an engaging, typewriter effect.\
- **File Attachment:** Supports sending attachments for more personalized interactions (if needed for educational purposes).\
- **Kid-Friendly Interactions:** Responses are tailored to be understandable and safe for children.\
\
## Requirements\
To set up and use Miraculous AI, you need your own OpenAI API key:\
\
1. **Get an API Key:** Register on [OpenAI's website](https://beta.openai.com/signup/) and create an API key.\
2. **Add the API Key:** Open the `app.js` file and replace the placeholder with your actual OpenAI API key:\
\
    ```javascript\
    const OPENAI_API_KEY = 'your-openai-api-key-here'; // Replace with your OpenAI API key\
    ```\
\
3. **Dependencies:** Ensure any necessary dependencies are installed if using additional libraries.\
\
## Setup Instructions\
1. **Clone the Repository:**\
    ```bash\
    git clone https://github.com/your-username/Miraculous-AI.git\
    ```\
2. **Navigate to the Project Directory:**\
    ```bash\
    cd Miraculous-AI\
    ```\
3. **Configure the API Key:** Update the `app.js` file with your OpenAI API key as mentioned above.\
4. **Open in Browser:** Launch the `index.html` file in a web browser to start the chat.\
\
## How to Use\
- **Ask Questions:** Kids can type questions or interact with the chatbot about various topics.\
- **Typewriter Effect:** The responses appear in a typewriter style to make reading fun.\
- **Educational Responses:** The assistant provides answers that are age-appropriate and engaging.\
\
